    "title": "Exponents and Radicals",
    "body": "Exponent rules let you combine powers. Multiplying powers with the same base adds exponents; dividing subtracts them; a power of a power multiplies them. A radical is a fractional exponent.",
    "key_points": [
      "aᵐ·aⁿ = aᵐ⁺ⁿ (add when multiplying).",
      "aᵐ/aⁿ = aᵐ⁻ⁿ (subtract when dividing).",
      "(aᵐ)ⁿ = aᵐⁿ (multiply for a power of a power)."
    ],
    "worked_example": "2³·2⁴ = 2⁷ = 128."
  },
